http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Organs-of-brain-dead-woman-donated/article13982385.ece

The family members of housewife G. Padma (38) from Nalgonda, who was admitted to Aware Global Hospital, L. B. Nagar with symptoms of a massive brain stroke and was declared brain dead, have decided to donate her organs under State-run Jeevandan scheme.On December 31, she was admitted with severe headache in an unconscious State to the hospital.After repeated attempts to revive her failed, the hospital neurosurgeons declared her as brain dead on Saturday, January 2.“When contacted, her family members agreed to donate organs,” in-charge, Jeevandan, Dr. G. Swarnalatha said.